  • Manufacturing internal, loaded, printed circuit board devices, such as sound, video, controller, and network interface cards; internal and external computer modems; and semiconductor storage devices, such as memory chips--are classified in Industry 33441, Semiconductor and Other Electronic Component Manufacturing;
  • Manufacturing other parts, such as casings, stampings, cable sets, and switches, for computers--are classified in the Manufacturing sector based on their associated production processes; and
  • Retailing computers with on-site assembly--are classified in Industry 449210, Electronics and Appliance Retailers.

